    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-13T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-13T15:00:00-05:00" n="1244"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1244">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4877.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Consul at Douglas</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-13T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1912—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Vice Consul Bowman reports that it is feared insurrectionists will attack
                    Nogales. If that seems likely communicate to him the substance of the
                    Department’s September 12, 8 p.m., to you, telling him to make the instructions
                    therein applicable to himself and to the situation in Nogales in the same way
                    that they are applicable to you and the situation at Aguaprieta.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
